reviews.text: Nice place with nice atmosphere. I rarely like or visit ‘attractions’ and seldomly recommend them. This one I do.
Gorgeous building, it looks like a fairytale building build on a tiny island on the river that crosses Bamberg. The whole town is pretty.

We were fortunate enough to have lunch at the Altes Rathaus Bamburg.  Our table overlooked the river and we could see the bridge that we had crossed earlier that had a spectacular view of this restaurant.  The food was delicious at this Bavarian restaurant.  Our entire Viking riverboat was served without a problem and they had room for many other guests.  Very impressive.

The building was placed on an artificial island, supposedly because the bishop didn’t want to relinquish any land. An armed conflict between the mayor and the bishop ended with an agreement that the citizens couldn’t rebuild their burned-down city hall on land. Tall arched bridges connect the island on either side to this city center on a river. Gorgeous place. Don’t miss it.
Lovely place to experience the outdoor art and vistas of the bridges and river. We did not tour the interior.

Really beautiful and in the heart of the city. You can walk from there to everything else in a circle a you will see everything that Dresden has to offer. There are pieces from the old church on the outside! If you head over there on Christmas time, check out their Christmas market it's small, but it's really beautiful. Try some of the locals favorites and enjoy it. Dresden is beautiful!

Beautiful "new" Lutheran Church, rebuilt fairly recently after the old one was destroyed in WWII. It's neat that architects and engineers used computer simulations of the destruction in order to incorporate the rubble into the reconstruction. You can tell the original stones because they are darker in colour than the rest.

Beautiful historical church with many events. (Open to visitors only a few hours a day on weekends.)
Viewing platform in the dome.
Touching exhibits in the crypt about its rebuilding after the bombing of Dresden.
The circolar and high Church. Beautiful incredible. Fantastic and magician Church in wonderful place Frauenkirche with many others beautiful building.
a very well preserved church. a centerpiece in Dresden. man can not miss it. If you are in or near Dresen, you have to visit

A Museum that ist dedicated for the history of Braunschweig. The exhibition is organized in chronical room from the Start of 18th century Braunschweig to Post war era. There are also some other exhibition at the Museum so Check in their Websites before your visit.
Lego!

Ein idealer Ort für Regentage mit Kindern. Das Personal dort ist sehr kinderfreundlich, es gibt viele Dinge für Kinder auszuprobieren: Klettern auf ein Schiff, Verkleiden wie Leute aus alten Zeiten, Rätsel und Ausmalen. Komischerweise scheint das eher ein Geheimtipp zu sein. Man sieht wenige andere Eltern mit kleinen Kindern dort.

Sehr schönes regionales Museum, das oftmals ganz besonders gut geplante und umgesetzte Sonderausstellungen bietet.

Ohne zu bezahlen kann man aber auch so regionale Geschichte bestaunen. Der Eiserne Heinrich steht wirklich in einem Bereich in dem man ihn kostenlos besichtigen kann. Eiserner Heinrich ist eine 3,90 m hohe Nagelfigur, die während des Ersten Weltkrieges in Braunschweig entstand. Wer sich die Zeit nimmt kann so einige Gravuren auf den Nägeln bekannten Größen zuordnen.

Fazit: Das ist der Hammer

Die derzeitige Ausstellung brutal modern gibt sehr viele Einblicke in die Architektur im Braunschweiger Land. Und wenn man den Besuch mit einer Führung kombiniert, ist es unglaublich interessant und kurzweilig.

If you are old enough you may recognize some of these toys from your childhood. To me, it was more about browsing intricate private collection than nostalgia. I still found couple toys from my childhood. This collection includes toys from all over the world. It has a nice cafe where you can take a break. Prepare to climb some stairs as it does not have an elevator (not wheelchair acessible), but this old historic building adds to the theme.
Good place to go especially for adults. They can recognize the politics of the last 100 years in toys.
A fascinating place to enjoy, a place full of details designed by passion whit unique smell for each room.

This toy museum is amazing. I saw toys from the 1850s to the 1960s across multiple different continents; handmade and factory produced.
Particular highlights:
- the hallway to the toilets looks like a submarine.
- a picture of the creator, Sunay Akin, as a young boy with a tin boat that a photographer gave him as a prop, but which the young boy thought was given to him as a souvenir! I can just imagine the conversation with a young boy to convince him to give the toy back!
- such well preserved toys from WWII, with a heartbreaking background.
Things to be aware of: 
- the museum is very crowded, tonnes of kids will be there
- the place is four or five stories but each level by itself is relatively small: you will spend a long time on each floor though because each display is packed full of little toys that will catch your eye.
- this place is NOT wheelchair friendly; there are no lifts and the stairs between each level are tiny, steep and winding without proper handrails.

Such an incredible place to see. Great toy collection from all around the world. Also it’s a nice coincidence with Mr. Akin, the founder of the Istanbul toy museum. He behaves so kind and friendly. You should read his books which contain great stories of the toys and people.

Always a great place for a party atmosphere. Such a fun place to go with a group. If you don't like it loud this place isn't for you. Good German food that's a bit pricey but you're paying for the entertainment aspects really.

A must try adventure in Vegas!

I'm not a beer drinker, and I don't like too much noise, so I went early to avoid the crowds. I wanted some good German food, and they didn't disappoint. The schnitzel and spätzle were both delicious, the wurst were fantastic, and the pretzel made me want to eat 5 more. The servers were very friendly and attentive. Wonderful place to visit, even if you're not into the beer/tavern scene.

Great food, very quick service. Traditional Octoberfest style seating. Friendly staff dressed in traditional garb. Live band that wasn't too loud. If I had to offer a criticism, the German rye bread was just a slice, not a warm, crusty miniature loaf. Still a great overall meal.

I have always had a great time here. Food is great, and the atmosphere is the best!

My only complaint is if you call for a reservation, ensure you request for the hall. I called, and was told it was not busy, so we did not need to make a reservation. We showed up and were told the only seats available were in the back biergarten.  

Service is great! No complaints at all, other than seating placement!

This place was amazing. I'm in Vegas on a work trip so had a group of 15 people. They easily accommodate big groups here. They have German music with entertainment the entire meal. The service was good, and the food was amazing. I'm super picky when it comes to food, but I ordered #365 and it was a pork platter with mashed potatoes and it's some of the best pork I've ever had will come back again next time in Vegas!

This restaurant is right definition of heaven. The food is delicious I ordered the steak with vegetables, herbal butter and wine sauce.
The steak was medium and juice just like I love it, the vegetables were flavorful and the butter on top was just perfect.
On the side I've got some yummy yummy crunchy french fries.
Now that was the food, the view outside this place is breathtaking, it was freezing outside but I couldn't help standing there to take it all in.
Service: great, the waitress was super nice and patient.

Good place with nice view of the city, you can sit at the restaurant or on the grass, whatever you prefer! Great place to bring your kids, because there is a playground just next to the restaurant. Nice service and staff 👌

The best view of Bern and an amazing atmosphere with a wood fire place on the inside and an outside covered area. Good service with an adequate range of spirits and wines. The waitress who served us was very nice. Hence I would say good service.
Beautiful, warm and comfortable tables, indoors and partially outdoors. Food is tremendous. The lamb steak must try.

Fantastic panorama spot, wide view over Bern, 5 minutes walk from Bus parking and tourist information. Start your Bern visit here at this sunshine spot with a cup of coffee & regional cakes. People of Berne love it as well, often busy. Outdoor Playground directly beside it.

They Lie to me NO Vegan Option & Waiting  There for Nothing waste of time at the Table. I Did NOT Like What Was on The Menu & it was Disgusting. So I left quick. I Did not want to be Seen There Either. Because I'm kinda famous. Definitely Not My Type Of Place.

I am vegan and one of my friends who went with me eats halal (my friend enjoyed the lamb). We loved the food and the experience so much that we came back the next night also. The staff and owners are very nice. Next time I am back in Albuquerque I will eat here again.

My favorite Indian food lunch buffet here in Albuquerque.  We make it a point to go meet at least once a month with our friends.  They have all the great stuff you'd expect at a Indian food buffet and they do a great job at all of it.  It's typically bustling and busy at lunch, but with several dining areas and attentive polite staff that are constantly on top of everything, it's always a pleasurable experience.

First time coming here, and first time eating Indian food, and I have to say that I loved it! The location is pretty old and might be in need for an update, but they make up for it with the great food. I went for lunch, and they have their buffet, which makes it really easy to get a sample of their offerings
Always wonderful!  Have been a patron for years, and it's always a good bet.  Had the baked eggplant and lamb meatballs.....great!  Always have an appetizer.
